<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401801>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 43–46. Habitats of Laccophilus leguyaderi sp. nov. (43–44) and Laccophilus bergsteni sp. nov. (45–46). (43) Shallow brooklet with peaty bottom in subalpine grassland (Andringitra massif, 2,000 m); (44) Rather deep brook with peaty bottom, slowly flowing among subalpine shrubs (Andringitra massif, 1,970 m; type locality of L. leguyaderi); (45) Slowly flowing stream in natural forest with muddy bottom and lots of tree leaves (Ankaratra massif, Tavolotara, 2,000 m); (46) Slowly flowing stream on flat area in subalpine grassland (Ankaratra massif, 2,400 m; type locality of L. bergsteni)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4401801/files/figure.png" .

